00:12:06,39 --> 00:12:08,41
Hi. What are you doing here?
你怎么来了？

175
00:12:08,69 --> 00:12:10,95
I was wondering, when you and I split up...
我在想，我们分手时

176
00:12:11,23 --> 00:12:15,29
...did you get the tape that was half the last episode of M.A. S.H...
你有没有分到一卷带子 录了最后一集的“外科医生”

177
00:12:15,53 --> 00:12:17,76
...and half the hostages coming home?
和人质回国的新闻？

178
00:12:19,13 --> 00:12:22,80
But now it's Susan and me in Mexico and the hostages coming home.
现在是苏珊和我游墨西哥 和人质回国的新闻

179
00:12:23,47 --> 00:12:24,30
Where's Ben?
班呢？

180
00:12:24,54 --> 00:12:25,77
He's sleeping.
在睡觉

181
00:12:27,98 --> 00:12:29,91
Is this a bad time?
我来得不是时候？

182
00:12:30,14 --> 00:12:32,98
Yeah,actually. Susan's gonna be here any minute.
没错，苏珊马上就要来了

183
00:12:33,21 --> 00:12:34,81
It's kind of an anniversary.
今天是个纪念日

184
00:12:35,48 --> 00:12:37,95
I thought you guys got married in January.
你们不是一月结婚？

185
00:12:38,15 --> 00:12:39,88
A different kind of anniversary.
是另一个纪念日

186
00:12:44,73 --> 00:12:46,42
So anyway
总之…

187
00:12:46,66 --> 00:12:48,59
Candles,champagne....
蜡烛、香槟

188
00:12:49,00 --> 00:12:51,40
Yeah,anniversaries are great...
纪念日真好

189
00:12:51,90 --> 00:12:54,39
... because love lasts forever, you know?
因为爱是永恒的

190
00:12:55,27 --> 00:12:58,47
There's nothing like it in this life. Money in the bank.
什么也比不上爱情可靠

191
00:12:58,74 --> 00:13:00,50
So Rachel and I broke up.
瑞秋和我分手了

192
00:13:02,01 --> 00:13:04,60
God,Ross,I am so sorry!
天哪，真可惜

193
00:13:06,08 --> 00:13:07,07
You know what?
你知道吗？

194
00:13:07,31 --> 00:13:09,34
I wanna talk about this so much...
我很想陪你聊一聊

195
00:13:09,58 --> 00:13:11,92
... but when we can really get into it.
但要找个能长谈的时间

196
00:13:12,12 --> 00:13:14,35
-You free for dinner tomorrow? -I'd love that.
明天晚餐可以吗？ 太好了

197
00:13:14,59 --> 00:13:15,52
Me too.
我也是

198
00:13:15,76 --> 00:13:19,35
I guess it all started when Rachel got this new job.
一切都是因为瑞秋找到新工作

199
00:13:21,86 --> 00:13:23,76
Triple A can pick us up.
汽车协会可以来载我们

200
00:13:24,00 --> 00:13:25,93
What town are we near?
我们靠近哪个镇？

201
00:13:26,17 --> 00:13:27,00
Freemont.
佛利蒙特

202
00:13:27,20 --> 00:13:28,63
Westmont.
威斯蒙特

203
00:13:29,10 --> 00:13:29,93
Westberg?
威斯柏格？

204
00:13:30,14 --> 00:13:32,04
Why are you answering?
不知道就别说

205
00:13:33,27 --> 00:13:34,94
Do you know what route we're on?
我们在哪条路上？

206
00:13:35,21 --> 00:13:38,20
We are definitely on Route 27.
绝对是27号公路

207
00:13:38,45 --> 00:13:41,44
We are at a rest stop on Route 27
我们在27号公路一个休息站

208
00:13:41,65 --> 00:13:43,38
There is no Route 27.
没有27号公路

209
00:13:43,62 --> 00:13:46,14
-Either 93 or 76. -I don't know.
不是93号就是76号 我不知道

210
00:13:46,39 --> 00:13:48,88
I always slept in the back when we drove here.
我每次来都在后座睡觉

211
00:13:50,06 --> 00:13:54,82
Can you just send someone up and down 76 and check every rest stop?
能不能请人 沿着76号公路找？

212
00:13:55,06 --> 00:13:56,86
And also 93?
还有93号公路？

213
00:13:59,70 --> 00:14:00,96
No,they don't do that.
他们不干

214
00:14:04,64 --> 00:14:06,47
Somebody will come and save us.
一定会有人来救我们

215
00:14:06,71 --> 00:14:10,04
Who? Have you seen a car in the last hour and a half?
谁？这一个半小时 有车子经过吗？

216
00:14:10,31 --> 00:14:13,41
We should call Ross. Maybe he can get a car to get us.
应该找罗斯 他可以借车来载我们

217
00:14:13,65 --> 00:14:15,88
I am not getting in a car with Ross!
我不要跟罗斯同车

218
00:14:16,15 --> 00:14:17,91
We will just have to...
我们必须…

219
00:14:18,15 --> 00:14:19,02
...Iive here!
耗在这里

220
00:14:20,52 --> 00:14:22,01
-But it's so cold. -No!
但是好冷 不行

221
00:14:22,22 --> 00:14:25,72
I won't get in a car with him. Think of something else.
我不跟他同车，想别的办法

222
00:14:25,99 --> 00:14:27,43
Joey and Chandler are back!
乔伊和钱德回来了

223
00:14:30,66 --> 00:14:33,00
So the "going for help" went well?
求援过程很顺利？

224
00:14:33,43 --> 00:14:37,34
Smokey Joe here got halfway to the highway and collapsed.
老烟枪走到一半就挂了

225
00:14:37,54 --> 00:14:39,84
I have the lung capacity of a 2-year-old.
我的肺活量跟两岁小孩一样

226
00:14:40,54 --> 00:14:41,94
Then why are you smoking?
那你为什么要抽烟？

227
00:14:42,18 --> 00:14:43,54
It's very unsettling.
我很不安

228
00:14:47,08 --> 00:14:49,61
Right? I mean, it's pretty unbelievable.
对吧？真是太扯了

229
00:14:49,92 --> 00:14:53,44
They just took off, without even looking back.
他们就这样头也不回的出发

230
00:14:54,29 --> 00:14:57,69
I don't need them. I've got you guys now as friends.
我不需要他们 我有你们这些朋友

231
00:14:57,93 --> 00:14:59,02
You and Susan.
你和苏珊

232
00:14:59,69 --> 00:15:01,92
Susan will be so pleased.
苏珊会很高兴

233
00:15:04,06 --> 00:15:05,62
Seven-one-seven?
717？

234
00:15:05,87 --> 00:15:07,36
Where's 717?
717是哪里？

235
00:15:10,10 --> 00:15:12,20
You have more of these for Susan,right?
你有帮苏珊留吧？

236
00:15:12,44 --> 00:15:13,91
No,but that's okay.
没有，不过没关系

237
00:15:14,11 --> 00:15:16,74
I'll just put out pickles or something.
还有酸黄瓜可以吃

238
00:15:20,95 --> 00:15:22,81
-Ross,thank God! -Pheebs?
罗斯，谢天谢地 菲比？

239
00:15:23,05 --> 00:15:24,54
Why are you whispering?
为什么这么小声？

240
00:15:25,12 --> 00:15:26,98
I ate a bug.
我吃了一只虫子

241
00:15:28,16 --> 00:15:30,92
Hey,Rach! The tampons here are only a penny.
瑞秋，这里的棉条只要一毛钱

242
00:15:31,13 --> 00:15:32,79
Let's stock up.
我们买来屯积

243
00:15:33,89 --> 00:15:38,16
We're out of gas and don't know where we are so we can't get a tow truck.
我们没油了，又不知道方位 没办法叫拖车

244
00:15:39,33 --> 00:15:41,10
Now you want a favor?
现在需要帮忙了？

245
00:15:41,30 --> 00:15:42,13
Yes,please.
对，拜托

246
00:15:42,34 --> 00:15:44,90
I'm sorry your car broke down,Pheebs...
很抱歉你们的车子挂了

247
00:15:45,17 --> 00:15:48,34
... but I'm too busy with some of my real friends right now.
但是我忙着跟真朋友联络感情

248
00:15:48,58 --> 00:15:51,41
But please call to let me know you got home safely.
等你们安全到家，记得通知我

249
00:15:51,61 --> 00:15:53,48
Phoebe,hang on a second.
菲比，等一下

250
00:15:53,75 --> 00:15:55,41
Take my car. Get your friends.
开我的车去接你朋友

251
00:15:55,62 --> 00:15:57,24
No,I won't pick them up.
我才不要去接他们

252
00:15:57,48 --> 00:16:00,48
We both know you'll do it, because you're not a jerk.
我们都知道你会去 因为你不是混蛋

253
00:16:00,75 --> 00:16:03,66
So you can sulk here for half an hour, then go get them...
你顶多再骂个半小时 还是会去接他们

254
00:16:03,96 --> 00:16:06,83
-...or save time and sulk in the car. -Rachel doesn't
不如节省时间去车上骂 瑞秋不会…

255
00:16:07,09 --> 00:16:09,26
I'm sorry Rachel dumped you for Mark...
很遗撼瑞秋为了马克甩了你

256
00:16:09,46 --> 00:16:11,99
...and you're the innocent victim in this.
你是无辜的受害者

257
00:16:12,27 --> 00:16:15,03
But don't punish your friends for what Rachel did.
但不要为了瑞秋牵怒你的朋友

258
00:16:17,47 --> 00:16:18,67
Yeah,you're right.
你说得对

259
00:16:19,31 --> 00:16:22,00
Phoebe,hang on. Ross wants to say something.
菲比，等一下，罗斯要跟你说

260
00:16:22,21 --> 00:16:23,04
What?
什么？

261
00:16:23,34 --> 00:16:24,94
You slept with someone else?
你跟别人上床？

262
00:16:26,88 --> 00:16:28,54
We were on a break!
我们当时在分手状态

263
00:16:30,05 --> 00:16:31,04
We were
我们…

264
00:16:32,22 --> 00:16:35,35
Where are you? I'll find you.
你们在哪里？我去找

265
00:16:35,62 --> 00:16:37,06
You slept with another woman?
你跟别的女人上床？

266
00:16:37,32 --> 00:16:39,88
Oh,you're one to talk.
你还敢说

267
00:16:44,40 --> 00:16:45,99
Okay,done!
好了

268
00:16:48,37 --> 00:16:49,30
What's "pleh"?
什么是“命救”？

269
00:16:50,47 --> 00:16:52,67
That's "help" spelled backwards...
就是“救命”反过来

270
00:16:52,87 --> 00:16:56,04
...so that the helicopters can read it from the air.
好让直升机上的人看得懂

271
00:16:58,21 --> 00:17:00,58
What's "dufus" spelled backwards?
“呆子”反过来怎么写？

272
00:17:03,35 --> 00:17:04,25
Car! Car!
有车子！

273
00:17:07,99 --> 00:17:10,58
Oh,it's Ross on one of his drives!
罗斯出来兜风了

274
00:17:12,43 --> 00:17:14,33
What is he doing here?
他来干什么？

275
00:17:14,56 --> 00:17:16,43
He is saving your butt.
他来救你们一命

276
00:17:16,73 --> 00:17:18,82
Unless I'm stepping on some toes here...
除非我惹到了某个人

277
00:17:19,03 --> 00:17:20,86
...in which case I could just mosey on.
那我可以闪人

278
00:17:21,10 --> 00:17:23,57
I have plenty of people to help on the interstate.
州际公路上有很多人需要帮助

279
00:17:23,77 --> 00:17:26,17
-Come on! -We need your help,please!
别这样 我们需要你

280
00:17:26,37 --> 00:17:28,34
Fine! Fine!
好好好

281
00:17:32,28 --> 00:17:35,77
Oh,no! Now it's not gonna make any sense.
完了，别人会看不懂

282
00:17:37,55 --> 00:17:38,85
You guys...
喂…

283
00:17:39,35 --> 00:17:42,29
...what do we do about Ross? He drove all the way up here.
罗斯怎么办？他大老远跑来

284
00:17:42,56 --> 00:17:44,79
Just send him back, then we'll go skiing?
难道要叫他回去 我们自己去滑雪？

285
00:17:45,06 --> 00:17:47,96
This is horrible. It's just horrible.
烦死了

286
00:17:48,56 --> 00:17:50,72
Should we ask Ross to come along?
要找罗斯一起去吗？

287
00:17:50,93 --> 00:17:54,03
But what about Rachel? How are we gonna even ask her?
那瑞秋呢？要怎么向她开口？

288
00:17:54,27 --> 00:17:55,86
Ask me what?
开什么口？

289
00:17:58,64 --> 00:18:01,44
If it might be okay if Ross came skiing?
罗斯能不能去滑雪？

290
00:18:01,98 --> 00:18:04,41
No,I wasn't gonna ask that.
我才没有要问

291
00:18:06,48 --> 00:18:09,54
You guys are unbelievable. No,he cannot come!
你们太扯了 不行，他不能去

292
00:18:09,78 --> 00:18:11,94
-Excuse me? -It's horrible!
什么？ 烦死了

293
00:18:12,49 --> 00:18:17,42
Oh,please? Can't I come to your special,magical cabin?
求求你，让我去你的神奇小屋

294
00:18:17,62 --> 00:18:21,32
Why would you even want to come? You're a horrible skier.
你去干什么？你滑雪滑得很烂

295
00:18:21,60 --> 00:18:24,33
Hitting me where it hurts! My ski skills!
真是说到我的痛处啊！

296
00:18:25,43 --> 00:18:26,56
Here we go again.
又来了

297
00:18:26,80 --> 00:18:28,39
I can't handle this,you guys.
我没办法处理

298
00:18:28,64 --> 00:18:30,83
I can handle it. "Handle" is my middle name.
我有办法 “处理”是我的名字

299
00:18:31,11 --> 00:18:34,63
Actually,it's the middle part of my first name.
我的名字去头去尾就是处理

300
00:18:36,31 --> 00:18:38,44
All right,Pheebs,your cab's ready.
菲比，你的车子好了

301
00:18:38,65 --> 00:18:39,63
Let's go.
走吧

302
00:18:40,51 --> 00:18:41,41
You're welcome.
不客气

303
00:18:41,62 --> 00:18:45,31
I'm sorry. Were you speaking to me, or sleeping with someone else?
抱歉，你在跟我说话 还是跟别人上床？

304
00:18:46,65 --> 00:18:47,85
We were on a break!
我们当时分手了

305
00:18:48,09 --> 00:18:51,65
Why don't you just put that on your answering machine?
你干脆在答录机里留这句话

306
00:18:51,86 --> 00:18:54,69
It's valid,and I'm not the only one who thinks so.
本来就是，不只我这么想

307
00:18:54,93 --> 00:18:56,12
Monica agrees with me.
摩妮卡也同意

308
00:18:56,86 --> 00:18:57,85
What?
什么？

309
00:18:58,83 --> 00:19:00,20
I don't know.
我不知道

310
00:19:01,50 --> 00:19:02,87
You said it last night.
你昨晚说的

311
00:19:03,27 --> 00:19:06,50
What I said was that I understood.
我是说我能理解

312
00:19:06,77 --> 00:19:09,61
Joey is the one who agreed with you.
乔伊才认同你

313
00:19:10,18 --> 00:19:11,51
Really,Joey?
是吗，乔伊？

314
00:19:13,05 --> 00:19:14,04
What?
什么？

315
00:19:15,18 --> 00:19:18,28
You know what? There is no right or wrong here.
这件事没有对错

316
00:19:18,49 --> 00:19:20,98
I think it's very obvious who's wrong here.
我觉得错的是谁很明显

317
00:19:21,19 --> 00:19:23,18
Obviously not to Joey.
乔伊不这么想

318
00:19:25,96 --> 00:19:26,98
What?
什么？

319
00:19:27,83 --> 00:19:32,06
-Joey and Monica feel the way I do! -You and this innocent puppy act!
乔伊和摩妮卡跟我感觉一样 你只会装无辜

320
00:19:32,97 --> 00:19:35,13
Hey,guess who I am?
你们猜我在学谁？

321
00:19:45,41 --> 00:19:47,85
Look what you're doing to Chandler!
你们把钱德害得多惨！

322
00:19:51,25 --> 00:19:55,15
Look. We know that this is really,really hard for you guys.
听着，我们知道你们都很难受

323
00:19:56,16 --> 00:19:58,15
You don't have to love each other.
你们不必爱对方

324
00:19:58,36 --> 00:20:02,02
You don't even have to like each other much right now.
你们现在甚至不必喜欢对方

325
00:20:02,23 --> 00:20:05,06
But please,find a way to be around each other.
但是请设法和平相处

326
00:20:05,27 --> 00:20:07,89
And not put us in the middle.
别让我们左右为难

327
00:20:08,10 --> 00:20:13,10
Otherwise,I mean,that's just it for us hanging out together.
否则我们以后就不用在一起了

328
00:20:13,34 --> 00:20:15,33
Is that what you want?
你们真的想这样？

329
00:20:17,28 --> 00:20:18,90
Can you be civil?
讲理一点好吗？

330
00:20:22,12 --> 00:20:23,28
I can.
我可以

331
00:20:24,69 --> 00:20:27,52
Good,let's get back in the car. It's freezing...
很好，回车上吧，冷死了

332
00:20:27,75 --> 00:20:29,52
...and my chest is unsupported.
我的胸部又吊在那边

333
00:20:30,56 --> 00:20:31,68
Wait a second!
等一下

334
00:20:31,93 --> 00:20:34,76
I mean,what are we doing? Who's going with who?
现在是怎样？谁要跟谁走？

335
00:20:38,77 --> 00:20:41,46
Look,you guys should go.
你们去吧

336
00:20:42,57 --> 00:20:44,97
You know, you planned this all out...
你们都计划好了

337
00:20:46,64 --> 00:20:49,20
...and I don't wanna ruin it. So just go.
我不想破坏，你们去吧

338
00:20:49,48 --> 00:20:51,54
You drove all the way up here.
你大老远开车来

339
00:20:51,78 --> 00:20:53,97
I've got to take the car back anyway.
反正我得去还车

340
00:20:54,25 --> 00:20:56,44
I'm spending all day tomorrow with Ben.
我明天一整天都要陪班

341
00:20:56,65 --> 00:21:00,88
It's fine,okay? Just go. No guilt,I promise.
没关系，你们去吧 不要有罪恶感，真的

342
00:21:02,92 --> 00:21:03,75
Thank you.
谢谢

343
00:21:06,43 --> 00:21:07,95
We'll call you when we get back.
回去再打电话给你

344
00:21:08,63 --> 00:21:11,83
Maybe we can,like, go to a movie or something.
我们可以去看电影

345
00:21:12,07 --> 00:21:13,59
Or the rodeo!
或是去看马术表演

346
00:21:15,57 --> 00:21:16,66
That would be great.
听起来不错

347
00:21:18,67 --> 00:21:21,84
I was being Shelley Winters from The Poseidon Adventure.
我在学“海神号”雪莉温特斯

348
00:21:24,14 --> 00:21:24,97
I know.
我知道

349
00:21:33,59 --> 00:21:34,65
Bye!
再见

350
00:22:00,38 --> 00:22:01,97
Hi. Sorry I'm late.
抱歉这么晚

351
00:22:02,32 --> 00:22:03,44
Were you sleeping?
你在睡觉？

352
00:22:04,75 --> 00:22:06,24
Oh,great.
那就好

353
00:22:07,39 --> 00:22:10,65
I had to get you a new battery. I got the best I could.
你的车子得换电池 我换了一个最好的

354
00:22:10,89 --> 00:22:12,72
You don't want to skimp there.
这种钱不能省

355
00:22:12,93 --> 00:22:14,05
You're a genius.
你真聪明

356
00:22:14,29 --> 00:22:15,76
It came to about $112.
花了112元

357
00:22:16,00 --> 00:22:18,40
But what the hell, call it an even 110?
算了，算110就好

358
00:22:19,80 --> 00:22:21,83
I'll pay you tomorrow. Bye!
明天给你，再见

359
00:22:22,07 --> 00:22:24,50
So they all took off.
他们都走了

360
